[
  {
    "ID": "6158",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "1",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "ٱلۡقَارِعَةُ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(1) The Striking Calamity -",
    "FOOTNOTES": ""
  },
  {
    "ID": "6159",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "2",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "مَا ٱلۡقَارِعَةُ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(2) What is the Striking Calamity?",
    "FOOTNOTES": ""
  },
  {
    "ID": "6160",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "3",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "وَمَآ أَدۡرَىٰكَ مَا ٱلۡقَارِعَةُ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(3) And what can make you know what is the Striking Calamity?",
    "FOOTNOTES": ""
  },
  {
    "ID": "6161",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "4",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "يَوۡمَ يَكُونُ ٱلنَّاسُ كَٱلۡفَرَاشِ ٱلۡمَبۡثُوثِ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(4) It is the Day when people will be like moths, dispersed,[1975]",
    "FOOTNOTES": "[1975]- The people will be as such after having been expelled from their graves."
  },
  {
    "ID": "6162",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "5",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "وَتَكُونُ ٱلۡجِبَالُ كَٱلۡعِهۡنِ ٱلۡمَنفُوشِ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(5) And the mountains will be like wool, fluffed up.[1976]",
    "FOOTNOTES": "[1976]- i.e., beginning to disintegrate."
  },
  {
    "ID": "6163",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "6",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "فَأَمَّا مَن ثَقُلَتۡ مَوَٰزِينُهُۥ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(6) Then as for one whose scales are heavy [with good deeds],",
    "FOOTNOTES": ""
  },
  {
    "ID": "6164",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "7",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "فَهُوَ فِي عِيشَةٖ رَّاضِيَةٖ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(7) He will be in a pleasant life.",
    "FOOTNOTES": ""
  },
  {
    "ID": "6165",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "8",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "وَأَمَّا مَنۡ خَفَّتۡ مَوَٰزِينُهُۥ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(8) But as for one whose scales are light,",
    "FOOTNOTES": ""
  },
  {
    "ID": "6166",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "9",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "فَأُمُّهُۥ هَاوِيَةٞ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(9) His refuge[1977] will be an abyss.[1978]",
    "FOOTNOTES": "[1977]- Literally, \"mother\" (a man's original refuge) , which will envelop him as in an embrace.\n[1978]- i.e., the pit of Hellfire."
  },
  {
    "ID": "6167",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "10",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "وَمَآ أَدۡرَىٰكَ مَا هِيَهۡ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(10) And what can make you know what that is?",
    "FOOTNOTES": ""
  },
  {
    "ID": "6168",
    "SURAH": "101",
    "AYAH": "11",
    "ARABIC_TEXT": "نَارٌ حَامِيَةُۢ",
    "TRANSLATION": "(11) It is a Fire, intensely hot.",
    "FOOTNOTES": ""
  }
]